  <div class="stage-intro">
    <h2>About this stage</h2>
    <p><strong>Platform-agnostic function.</strong> SHAPE operates across all products. It is where the market is understood, where demand is generated, and where new products may be conceived based on feedback from MEASURE.</p>
    <p>Key activities: identifying which conditions or pathways to prioritise next, building commissioner confidence and capability, running engagement cycles, and translating performance data into strategic direction.</p>
    <p>This is the entry point for the iterative loop. Without SHAPE receiving and acting on MEASURE outputs, the model is linear and static. With it, the platform continuously adapts.</p>
  </div>

  <h2 class="section-title">Current Status</h2>

  <div class="status-section progress-section">
    <div class="status-heading heading-progress">
      <span class="status-dot dot-progress"></span>
      In Progress
      <span class="status-count">8 items</span>
    </div>
    <ul class="status-list progress">
      <li>HIV live in Private Beta. Two LA + supplier pairings live (Salford LA with SH:24, East Sussex CC with Preventx). GDS Alpha Assessment complete. Public Beta window December 2026 to March 2027</li>
      <li>PME closed. 32 organisations of mixed type and size registered interest. Responses being collated. RFI issued to market. Three clarification questions subsequently received and answered (CQC pre-requisite, clinical lead requirement, digital integration cost)</li>
      <li>Supplier Forum scheduled for 8 July 2026. Three-block agenda confirmed: onboarding and assurance, post-result clinical handover, logistics and cold chain</li>
      <li>Commissioner engagement plan being prioritised. Discovery priorities confirmed: commissioner first, supplier, then patient. Three commissioner types identified: paying customers, pathway transformers, remote managers</li>
      <li>Plymouth/Devon NHS partnership visit completed. Royal Devon has acute self-sample pathways, high-sensitivity PSA analysers, capillary vs venous equivalence studies, NIHR centre. Draft EOI produced to partner as NHS clinical partner, not commercial supplier</li>
      <li>Pathway 2 sprint zero underway. PSA confirmed as the secondary care use case. Year 1 targets: 100 users, 2 trusts. Separate discovery track running parallel to HomeTest HIV</li>
      <li>Co-design workshops completed pre-Beta</li>
      <li>Deliverables stocktake: team aligning weekly update to 12-week plan deliverables per work package. Artefact list being consolidated for SLT accessibility</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="status-section open-section">
    <div class="status-heading heading-open">
      <span class="status-dot dot-open"></span>
      Open Decisions
      <span class="status-count">4 items</span>
    </div>
    <ul class="status-list open">
      <li>How the MEASURE feedback loop formally feeds into SHAPE (not yet designed)</li>
      <li>How change management operates within SHAPE</li>
      <li>Which conditions/pathways to prioritise after PSA. Five initiation patterns now codified in the HomeTest Prioritisation Framework (endorsed 9 June 2026): self-initiated, secondary care, community/GP, genomics, programme/system-initiated. Commissioner appetite for non-HIV pathways untested with actual acute commissioners or pathway owners</li>
      <li>Whether NHSE has the internal capability to run SHAPE as an ongoing function. The Dynamic Market/Framework delivers ASSURE, CONTRACT and FULFIL. SHAPE and MEASURE sit with NHSE as permanent capability. Whether that capability is built in-house or outsourced is unresolved</li>
    </ul>
